			</td><td width="2%">&nbsp;</td><td width="44%"> Abstract
			<div style="text-align:justify;">
				<P>
					<B>Introduction</B>: The aim of the study was to analyze the quality of life perceived by teachers of health of a private higher education institution . Quality of life (QOL ) is an association between general aspects of the subject with the environment they live in , it depends on personal decisions 
(heredity and lifestyle ) and government (education , environment and labor, among others).					<B>Objectives</B>: The aim of the study was to analyze the quality of life perceived by teachers of health of a private higher education institution . Quality of life (QOL ) is an association between general aspects of the subject with the environment they live in , it depends on personal decisions 
 heredity and lifestyle ) and government (education , environment and labor, among others).					<B>Methods</B>: This research is characterized as a descriptive exploratory study. Two (02) questionnaires for data collection were used. For the evaluation of the perception of QWL will use the "Quality of Life Assessment Scale on Perceived Work for Teacher Education Elementary School Physics and East" (QVT-PEF), developed by BOTH et al. (2006). The QVT-PEF comprises a questionnaire composed of 34 questions, divided into eight dimensions (Remuneration and compensation, working conditions, opportunity for immediate use and development of human capabilities, future opportunity for growth and security, social integration in work organization, Constitutionalism the organization of work, work and total life space, social relevance of life at work), which are based on the analysis matrix developed by Walton (1973 and 1974). In assessing the Lifestyle will apply the "Profile Individual Life Style" (pevi) that was developed by Nahas, Barros and Francalacci (2000) inspired by the Pentacle model Welfare. The pevi includes 15 questions spread across five components, which assess the food (nutrition), physical activity, preventive behavior, social relationships and the Control of Stress. A Microsoft Excel spreadsheet was used in tabulating the categorization of the data related to the dimensions / components and the overall assessment of both the QVT-PEF as the pevi. The statistical analysis was operationalized in SPSS 20 for Windows program.					<B>Results</B>: 					<B>Conclusion</B>: 				</P>
